# {{ project_name }} — Go + Fiber Backend

## Stack
- **Language**: Go 1.23
- **Framework**: Fiber v2
- **Database**: database/sql + sqlc
- **Migrations**: golang-migrate
- **Testing**: testing (stdlib) + testify

## Commands
- `go run ./cmd/{{ project_name }}` — Start server
- `go test ./...` — Run all tests
- `go fmt ./...` — Format code
- `go vet ./...` — Run static analysis
- `migrate -path migrations -database $DATABASE_URL up` — Run migrations

## Structure
- `cmd/` — Application entry points
- `internal/handler/` — HTTP handlers
- `internal/service/` — Business logic
- `internal/repository/` — Data access
- `internal/model/` — Domain models
- `migrations/` — SQL migration files
- `sql/` — sqlc query definitions
